## Cryptographic primitives

Verixa's signing and sealing operations rely on:

- **PyNaCl** — Python binding to `libsodium`. Licensed under **Apache-2.0**. Copyright (c) The PyNaCl developers. Source: <https://github.com/pyca/pynacl>
- **libsodium** — bundled by PyNaCl. Licensed under **ISC**. Copyright (c) Frank Denis. Source: <https://github.com/jedisct1/libsodium>
- **cryptography** (pyca/cryptography) — Licensed under **Apache-2.0 OR BSD-3-Clause** (dual). Copyright (c) Individual contributors. Source: <https://github.com/pyca/cryptography>

These three projects implement every cryptographic operation in Verixa. We rely on their security guarantees; Verixa does not implement custom cryptography. See [ADR-0004](docs/07_system_architecture/adr/ADR-0004-ed25519-over-rsa-for-dossier-signing.md).

